HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 292
BY REPRESENTATIVE KERNER
SEAFOOD: Memorializes the federal government to address unsafe imported seafood
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To memorialize the United States Department of Commerce and the National Oceanic and
3 Atmospheric Administration to take such actions as are necessary to properly inspect
4 and ensure the safety of imported seafood.
5 WHEREAS, the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) discovered in August of 2025
6 that imported shrimp being sold in United States grocery stores was radioactive; and
7 WHEREAS, several days later, at different grocery stores, the FDA found again that
8 tens of thousands of packages of radioactive frozen shrimp products were being sold to
9 United States consumers; and
10 WHEREAS, the FDA confirmed in August that imported seafood was contaminated
11 with Caesium-137, which is a radioactive isotope; and
12 WHEREAS, inspections of imported seafood are conducted by the National Oceanic
13 and Atmospheric Administration which is within the United States Department of
14 Commerce; and
15 WHEREAS, only one or two percent of imported seafood products are actually
16 inspected on a daily basis while countries such as the United Kingdom and China inspect
17 around half of their imported seafood products; and
18 WHEREAS, the domestic shrimp industry has long been critical of foreign shrimp
19 imports pointing out the amount of shrimp stopped by United States Customs and Border
20 Control for containing antibiotics and other contaminants; and
